title._content: U.S. Senator from Kansas Robert Dole, Stands on a Pick-Up Truck Bed Which Is One of the Parade Units in Cottonwood Falls Kansas, near Emporia...06/1974

description._content: Original Caption: U.S. Senator from Kansas Robert Dole, Stands on a Pick-Up Truck Bed Which Is One of the Parade Units in Cottonwood Falls Kansas, near Emporia. It Is a Part of the Flint Hills Rodeo Festivities and an Annual Cultural Event of Major Importance in the Area. It Is a 19th Century "Cowboy" Town in the Heart of the Kansas Flint Hills Region, and near an Area Designated as a Possible Site for a Tallgrass Prairie National Park 06/1974 U.S. National Archives’ Local Identifier: 412-DA-14607 Photographer: Duncan, Patricia D., 1932- Subjects: Emporia (Lyon county, Kansas, United States) inhabited place Environmental Protection Agency Project DOCUMERICA Persistent URL: arcweb.archives.gov/arc/action/ExternalIdSearch?id=557059 Repository: Still Picture Records Section, Special Media Archives Services Division (NWCS-S), National Archives at College Park, 8601 Adelphi Road, College Park, MD, 20740-6001.
